  "prompt": "Can an overdose of Bisoprolol kill you?",
  "response": "Yes, an overdose of Bisoprolol can potentially be fatal. Bisoprolol is a beta-blocker used to treat conditions such as high blood pressure and heart problems. Overdosing on Bisoprolol can lead to severe consequences, including excessively low blood pressure, slow heart rate (bradycardia), heart failure, bronchospasm, and other serious cardiovascular issues. In extreme cases, these effects can be life-threatening.\n\nIf an overdose is suspected, it is crucial to seek emergency medical attention immediately. Prompt medical intervention can be lifesaving and may include specific treatments to counteract the effects of the overdose. It's important to take medications exactly as prescribed and consult healthcare professionals with any concerns about dosing.",
